Then $\angle MPN = 180^\circ - \angle MPQ - \angle QPN = 48^\circ,$ so $\angle PMN = \boxed{84^\circ}.$

Since $\triangle PMR$ is isosceles, $\angle PMR = \angle PRM = 66^\circ.$  Then $\angle QRP = 180^\circ - 48^\circ - 66^\circ = 66^\circ.$

